	<string name="splash_payoff_line">Light-Weight Twitter, pump.io and StatusNet Client for Android™</string>
	<string name="splash_text_learn_more_1"><h1><b>AndStatus User Guide</b></h1>\n\n
        <h2><b>1. Getting started</b></h2>\n\n
        In order to start using the application, you must add at least one \"AndStatus\" 
        account to your device the same way you add Google accounts.\n
        Press \"Get Started\" button below and select the \"Manage accounts\" option
        in the AndStatus preferences <i>or</i> simply go to the \"Settings\" of Your device, 
        select \"Add account\" option and add an account of the \"AndStatus\" type.\n
        You will be prompted to select desired Microblogging system 
        (twitter, pump.io or StatusNet) 
        and authorise the AndStatus application\'s access to it
        at the Microblogging system\'s web site.\n 
        Please note that currently for \"StatusNet\" only \"Basic auhentication\" works; i.e. no OAuth.\n
        After successful creation of the account please launch AndStatus application again. 
        This time you will be presented with the Change Log. 
        Press the \"Get Started\" button below - and you will get to the main AndStatus window.\n
        Congratulations! Read below what you can do further.\n\n
        And don\'t forget to add AndStatus widget to the Home screen: 
        the widget will inform you about new messages and may be used to launch AndStatus.\n\n        
        <h2><b>2. AndStatus BASICS</b></h2>\n\n
        The first view of AndStatus contains the Home timeline.\n
        In order to perform an action on a message in the list you should <b>hold down</b>
        on it to get a context menu.\n
        You may <b>click</b> on a message to get more details on it or to see
        a conversation thread to which the message belongs.\n
        Press the <b>Menu</b> button on your device to switch to other views.\n\n
        <h2><b>3. SENDING AND REPLYING</b></h2>\n\n
        In order to update your status, press the \"Blog\" button (\"Tweet\" for Twitter),
        type in a text into the text area at the bottom of the screen and click <b>Send</b>.\n
        In order to reply, <b>hold down</b> a message and select <b>Reply</b>,
        type in your reply at the bottom.\n
        To abort a reply, simply press the \"Blog/Tweet\" button to hide the text area.\n\n
        <h2><b>4. DIRECT MESSAGES</b></h2>\n\n
        Click <b>Home</b> (Timeline type) button and select <b>Direct Messages</b>.\n
        In order to <b>delete</b> a direct message, <b>hold down</b> on it
        and select <b>Delete</b>.\n
        New messages are fetched if you have turned on <b>Automatic Updates</b>
        in Preferences. In any case you may always get updates from the Internet
        manually using \"Reload\" command in the Menu.\n\n
        <h2><b>5. LISTING MENTIONS</b></h2>\n\n
        Click <b>Home</b> and then <b>Mentions</b>.\n
        Mentions will list every message that mentions your <b>@username</b>.\n\n
        <h2><b>6. SEARCHING</b></h2>\n\n
        Click <b>Menu</b> and then <b>Search</b>, or you can click the <b>Search</b> button
        on your phone.\n
        A search will find any text contained within a message. 
        If you wish to show messages from a specific user, search for \"<b>username</b>.\"\n
        To see mentions of a specific user, search for \"<b>@username</b>\".\n\n
        </string>
